         <section-title>Special rules of classification</section-title>
         <section-body><paragraph-text type="body">Permanently installed large devices for obtaining water from humid air are classified in <class-ref scheme="cpc">E03B3/28</class-ref>, whereas devices for obtaining water from humid air which are mobile and/or combined with water treatment are classified in <class-ref scheme="cpc">C02F9/20</class-ref> .</paragraph-text><paragraph-text type="body">Intake structures in lakes are classified in <class-ref scheme="cpc">E03B3/04</class-ref>.</paragraph-text><paragraph-text type="body">Rainwater collecting tanks are classified in <class-ref scheme="cpc">E03B3/03</class-ref>. Accessories for the collection of rainwater, e.g. filters, inlet devices into the tank, are classified in <class-ref scheme="cpc">E03B3/02</class-ref>.</paragraph-text></section-body>
      </special-rules></definition-item>
